comment: Howard (HOU) and Vucevic (ORL) briefly engage and then separate.
Ariza (HOU) makes incidental contact with Vucevic (ORL) that does not affect his FOM.
Oladipo (ORL) makes incidental contact with Lawson (HOU) while attempting to rebound the ball.
RHH and RATR show Lawson (HOU) extends his hip into Harris (ORL) as he sets the hand-off screen, and doesn't give him room to avoid the contact.
Howard (HOU) makes incidental contact with Payton (ORL) that does not affect his movement to the basket or shot attempt.
Harden (HOU) steps toward Oladipo (ORL) as he is retreating and extends his arm to gain space. Oladipo's movement backwards does not appear to be commensurate with the level of contact.
Howard (HOU) sets the screen on Oladipo (ORL), clamping his arms and limiting his ability to get over the screen.
Vucevic (ORL) sets the screen on Lawson (HOU) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LATR shows that Harden (HOU) makes contact with Payton's (ORL) arm, causing him to lose control of the ball.
Howard (HOU) and Payton (ORL) have simultaneous possession of the ball and a jump ball is correctly called.
Fournier (ORL) makes contact with Beverley's (HOU) body and arm, affecting his jump shot attempt.
Howard (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position on Vucevic (ORL) and does not affect his RSBQ.
Fournier (ORL) gathers the ball on his right foot. His next step (left) is his first step after the gather, followed by his second step (right).

LHH shows Beverley (HOU) maintains a legal guarding position during Fournier's (ORL) drive; Beverley is permitted to apply a forearm to Fournier in the LBD to maintain his defensive position and he does not affect his RSBQ on the drive.
Howard (HOU) sets the screen on Oladipo (ORL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Harris (ORL) and Howard (HOU) make incidental contact as they attempt to get the rebound.
Ariza (HOU) commits a take foul on Payton (ORL).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball was last touched by Ariza (HOU) was confirmed and 00:01.1 put on the game clock.
Lawson (HOU) commits a take foul on Harris (ORL). Since the foul occurs before the touch, no time is taken off the clock (time is put back on during free throws).
Oladipo (ORL) and Harden (HOU) briefly engage and separate during the inbounds play.
Fournier (ORL) and Harris (ORL) legally contest Thornton's (HOU) jump shot attempt.
